devdoc.details: This is useful because it allows clients to filter out follow NFTs that were transferred to a recipient by another user (i.e. Not a mint) and not register them as "following" unless the recipient explicitly toggles the follow here.

params.profileId: The profile ID to query the metadata URI for.

returns._0: string The metadata associated with that profile ID, or an empty string if it is not set or the profile does not exist.

params.metadata: The metadata string to set for the profile.
params.profileId: The profile ID to set the metadata for.

params.vars: A SetProfileMetadataWithSigData struct containingthe regular parameters and an EIP712Signature struct.

params.enables: The array of booleans to enable/disable follows.
params.profileIds: The token ID array of the profiles.

params.vars: A ToggleFollowWithSigData struct containing the regular parameters as well as the signing follower's address and an EIP712Signature struct.
